itle\":\"Do they provide the equipment like helmets and jackets?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"},{\"title\":\"How many miles do I have to drive?\",\"content\":\"About 100\"},{\"title\":\"Can children travel?\",\"content\":\"Yes, they can travel with a parent and must be at least 10 years old.\"},{\"title\":\"What are the requirements for driving?\",\"content\":\"European licence (or international licence) valid to drive a car (B) or a motorbike (A) In Italy the car licence obtained abroad is valid to drive a Motorbike with power up to 15 HP (Traffic Police, doc. \\\"Codice della strada\\\" art. A2.3.3)\"},{\"title\":\"What Vespa do we rent?\",\"content\":\"The Vespa is a new Spring 125 cc model! We also have some 50 cc\"}]',22,22,'2020-05-02 03:59:31','2020-05-02 04:00:27','{\"0\":{\"title\":\"Vespa rental for the day\"},\"2\":{\"title\":\"Road book and tips on the territory to visit\"},\"3\":{\"title\":\"Helmets under helmets and windproof jacket.\"},\"4\":{\"title\":\"Basket of typical products and bottle of Prosecco DOCG for Vespa\"}}',NULL,'[{\"image_id\":\"423\",\"title\":\"Mermaids Bay\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"Along the lake of Santa Croce you will find wonderful bays: Bay of the Sirens, Bay Watch for surfers, Camping Sarathei for Kite Surfer. The colour of the water is constantly changing from green to turquoise.\"},{\"image_id\":\"426\",\"title\":\"The Vajont dam and the 1963 disaster\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"The Vajont disaster was the event that occurred on the evening of 9 October 1963 in the new Vajont artificial hydroelectric basin, due to the fall of a colossal landslide from the overhanging slope of Mount Toc into the waters of the Alpine lake basin of the same name.\\r\\nThe consequent overflow of the water contained in the reservoir, with the effect of washouting the lake shores and overcoming the dam, caused the flooding and destruction of the inhabitants of the Veneto valley floor, in particular Longarone, and the death of about 1,917 people.\"},{\"image_id\":\"428\",\"title\":\"Erto and Casso\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"To explore! Two countries frozen in time, frozen by a huge tragedy. Already ancient at the time of the disaster, they preserve the mystery and suffering of people who have lived a hard history and you can still understand the hurry in which they were abandoned. Written signs and firm feelings in the distant 1963.\"},{\"image_id\":\"427\",\"title\":\"Barcis\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"It is a stretch of water of artificial origin situated in Valcellina, at an altitude of 402 metres; on its northern shore is the village of Barcis. It was created in 1954 for the exploitation of hydroelectric energy; it is very well known not only for its waters coloured between green and sky-blue but also for legends and apparitions of fairy lights.\"},{\"image_id\":\"413\",\"title\":\"Sources of Gorgazzo\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"The spring is fed by the waters that, having sunk into the cracks of the Cansiglio or Monte Cavallo plateau, reappear on the surface. The Gorgazzo spring is a completely submerged cave.\\r\\nIn the pool\'s stretch of water, you can admire practically all the shades of blue: from the lightest blue to the darkest overseas, all seasoned with an emerald green that subdues the eye. A play of colours possible thanks to the continuous movement of the leaves due to the wind and the consequent filtering of light.\"}]'),(43,55,'en','The Asparago from Badoere IGP','','<p>Guided visit to a farm producing the prized Asparago from Badoere IGP: explanation of the cultivation and processing techniques of the fantastic vegetable, with demonstration of the various stages and production and processing with emotional and experiential involvement for the participant. To follow lunch in a typical restaurant where a themed tasting menu of asparagus and other local specialities awaits you.</p>\n<p> </p>',NULL,'Treviso','[{\"title\":\"What are the available days?\",\"content\":\"Monday to Saturday - Sunday on request for groups. Holidays are excluded\"},{\"title\":\"Where does the tour start?\",\"content\":\"At the scheduled company that will be communicated to the booking confirmation\"},{\"title\":\"Is it recommended for children?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"},{\"title\":\"At what time?\",\"content\":\"From 10 A.M. to 2 P.M.\"},{\"title\":\"Suitable for disabled people?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"}]',22,NULL,'2020-05-02 04:06:07','2020-05-02 04:06:07','[{\"title\":\"Available languages: Italian, English, French, German, Italian\"},{\"title\":\"Visit to a farm\"},{\"title\":\"Welcome drink\"},{\"title\":\"Final product tasting\"},{\"title\":\"3-course menu\"}]','[{\"title\":\"Transportation\"},{\"title\":\"Extras\"}]',NULL),(44,56,'en','Veneta Villas & degustation','','<p>Guided tour of Villa Marignana Benetton, a splendid and unexplored Venetian villa with its magnificent private park and the stories of the noble Venetian families who spent their summer holidays in these splendid residences in the 18th century. After visiting the interior rooms of the villa, you will walk with our guide through the park which covers an area of about 20,000 square meters, where art, history and nature coexist. Immersed in the rich flora of the place are alternated the peculiar historical elements such as the ancient ice house, built inside a small hill surmounted by a real well for air exchange and the large iron sculptures. About 70 works created between 1951 and 1995 by master Toni Benetton enrich the park, contributing to the magical atmosphere that, from season to season, dresses the landscape again. A truly magical place where history, art and nature merge into a single element.</p>\n<p>To complete the visit, tasting of excellent local wines such as Prosecco, Raboso, etc. combined with local cheese and cold cuts at a nearby winery.</p>',NULL,'Mogliano Veneto','[{\"title\":\"What are the available days?\",\"content\":\"Monday to Saturday - Sunday on request for groups. Holidays are excluded\"},{\"title\":\"Where does the tour start?\",\"content\":\"At the scheduled company that will be communicated to the booking confirmation\"},{\"title\":\"Is it recommended for children?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"},{\"title\":\"At what time?\",\"content\":\"From 10 A.M. to 1 P.M.\"},{\"title\":\"Suitable for disabled people?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"}]',22,NULL,'2020-05-02 04:11:47','2020-05-02 04:11:47','[{\"title\":\"Available languages: Italian, English, French, German, Italian\"},{\"title\":\"Scheduled visit to the farm\"},{\"title\":\"Entrance to the villa\"},{\"title\":\"Final tasting of wine and typical products\"}]','[{\"title\":\"Trasportation\"},{\"title\":\"Extras\"}]',NULL),(45,51,'en','Trout and Sturgeons','','<p>Guided tour of a trout farm, a unique example of trout and sturgeon farming and many other freshwater fish, located within the Sile River Nature Park. In the company of our guide, who will explain step by step the stages of the visit to the trout farm, the visitor will be guided along a training and entertainment path where it will be possible to learn about the stages of trout breeding and management from the spawning stage to the breeding stage. The visit ends with lunch in a typical restaurant where a themed tasting menu based on trout and other local specialities awaits you.</p>\n<p> </p>',NULL,'Treviso','[{\"title\":\"What are the available days?\",\"content\":\"From Monday to Saturday - Holidays are excluded\"},{\"title\":\"Where does the tour start?\",\"content\":\"At the scheduled company that will be communicated to the booking confirmation\"},{\"title\":\"Is it raccomented for children?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"},{\"title\":\"At what time?\",\"content\":\"From 10 A.M. TO 2 P.M.\"},{\"title\":\"Is it suitable for disable people?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"}]',22,NULL,'2020-05-02 04:15:46','2020-05-02 04:15:46','[{\"title\":\"Lingue disponibili: Italiano, Inglese, Francese, Tedesco\"},{\"title\":\"Visita ad una azienda agricola\"},{\"title\":\"Aperitivo di benvenuto\"},{\"title\":\"Degustazione finale dei prodotti\"},{\"title\":\"Men\\u00f9 3 portate\"}]','[{\"title\":\"Trasporto\"},{\"title\":\"Extra\"}]',NULL),(46,65,'en','Piazza San Marco - Palazzo Ducale e Rialto','','<p>Meeting with our guide in St. Mark\'s Square, this morning you will explore the area of St. Mark\'s Square and Rialto, to have a first introduction to the magnificence of Venice (4 hours walk). </p>\n<p>You will depart from St Mark\'s Square, the former political centre of the Republic of Venice, and then enter the Gothic Doge\'s Palace, once the seat of government, where the Doge, the \'head of the Serenissima\', resided and together with his advisors and politicians decided the fate of Europe in the 15th and 16th centuries. We admire in the courtyard the imposing Scala dei Giganti, climb the magnificent Renaissance Golden Staircase and reach the wonderful rooms decorated with paintings by Veronese, Tintoretto and Titian. We cross the famous Bridge of Sighs to cross the empty cells of the former prison building (approx. 1 hour and 15 minutes). </p>\n<p>We then continue with a visit to St. Mark\'s Basilica with its breathtaking mosaics and visit the spectacular Pala d\'Oro (approx. 30 -40 min).  </p>\n<p>Leaving the Basilica, through narrow and quiet side streets, you will see a slightly inclined bell tower in the distance and we will arrive in front of a fascinating hidden spiral staircase from the early Renaissance. </p>\n<p>Through the main shopping street you will reach the oldest bridge over the Grand Canal, the Rialto Bridge. You will finally discover how the Venetians dominated part of the Mediterranean thanks to the luxury goods imported from the Far East and admire the former \"shopping centre\", where the lively fruit, vegetable and fish market can still be found today.</p>',NULL,'Venice','[{\"title\":\"What are the available days?\",\"content\":\"Every day. Holidays are excluded\"},{\"title\":\"Where does the tour start?\",\"content\":\"Piazza San Marco, Porta della Carta of the Doge\'s Palace (which corresponds to the exit of the Doge\'s Palace)\"},{\"title\":\"Is it recommended for children?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"},{\"title\":\"At what time?\",\"content\":\"From 9 A.M. to 1 P.M.\"}]',22,22,'2020-05-03 04:33:53','2020-05-03 04:36:41','{\"0\":{\"title\":\"Available languages: Italian, English, French, German, Italian\"},\"6\":{\"title\":\"Guide available 4 hours\"},\"7\":{\"title\":\"Entrance to the Ducal Palace\"},\"8\":{\"title\":\"Entrance skip line to St Mark\'s Basilica\"},\"9\":{\"title\":\"Visit to the Scala del Bovolo (outside only)\"},\"10\":{\"title\":\"Visit to the Rialto market (not on Sundays)\"}}','[{\"title\":\"Trasportation\"},{\"title\":\"Extras\"}]',NULL),(47,63,'en','“Andar par e fodere” - Venice from the Venetians','','<p>Discover walking around the most unusual and characteristic corners of Venice!</p>\n<p>Do you want to be accompanied along an unusual and alternative itinerary that will make you discover a less known Venice? Our expert guide will take you on an unusual visit (outside only) and let you explore the most curious and less frequented corners of Venice!</p>',NULL,'Venice','[{\"title\":\"What are the available days?\",\"content\":\"Every day. Holidays are excluded\"},{\"title\":\"Where does the tour start?\",\"content\":\"Piazza San Marco, Porta della Carta of the Doge\'s Palace (which corresponds to the exit of the Doge\'s Palace)\"},{\"title\":\"Is it recommended for children?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"},{\"title\":\"At what time?\",\"content\":\"From 9 A.M. to 11 A.M.\\r\\nfrom 5 P.M. to 7 P.M.\"}]',22,NULL,'2020-05-03 04:44:29','2020-05-03 04:44:29','{\"0\":{\"title\":\"Available languages: Italian, English, French, German, Italian\"},\"6\":{\"title\":\"Guide available 2 hours\"}}','[{\"title\":\"Transportation\"},{\"title\":\"Extras\"}]',NULL),(48,62,'en','Gastronomic and cultural summer: Peseggia\'s peas, villas and gardens','','<p>You will discover with us the farms of the territory, the products, the wine, the cheese, the Venetian villas and the city of Treviso.</p>\n<p> </p>',NULL,NULL,'[{\"title\":\"Where?\",\"content\":\"Arrival by your own vehicle in the Treviso area, you will be notified of the exact location at the time of booking.\"},{\"title\":\"Is it always available?\",\"content\":\"The tour can be done from June 1st to July 31st.\"},{\"title\":\"For travel?\",\"content\":\"They\'re in their own vehicles or rental cars. The request must be made at the time of booking\"}]',22,22,'2020-05-03 04:48:29','2020-05-03 04:51:28','[{\"title\":\"visits to a fruit and vegetable company with demonstration and active participation\"},{\"title\":\"visits to a dairy with final tasting of products\"},{\"title\":\"visit to a winery with guided tastings of 3 wines\"},{\"title\":\"guided tour of an 18th century Venetian villa, including the entrance ticket\"},{\"title\":\"2 lunches based on typical products, excluding drinks\"},{\"title\":\"1 goodbye dinner, 1 welcome glass of prosecco included, drinks excluded\"},{\"title\":\"guided tour of Treviso\"}]','[{\"title\":\"Accommodation\"},{\"title\":\"Transport, possible quotation on request\"}]','[{\"image_id\":\"257\",\"title\":\"Day 1\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"I arrive with my own vehicle in the Treviso area. In the morning visit to a farm that produces some of the PGI products of the area including Piselli di Peseggia and other typical fruit and vegetable delicacies of the area. Demonstration of the processing phases of the products with active participation by the customer.\\r\\nLunch in a typical restaurant based on local specialties.\\r\\nIn the afternoon guided visit to a Venetian villa of the \\\"700 where you will also discover the wonderful park and a truly original collection of contemporary iron art sculptures.\\r\\nOvernight stay in a Hotel\\/Agriturismo in the area.\"},{\"image_id\":\"258\",\"title\":\"Day 2\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"In the morning visit to a cheese factory where the cheeses are all made with artisan techniques, aimed at preserving the scents and flavours of the ancient art of cheese making: ricotta la casatella, dairy cheese, caciotta, drunk cheese, mascarpone, to keep alive the memories of the lands of the Marca trevigiana and those who have lived them. \\r\\nWe continue with a visit to the nearby wine cellar, which is peculiar for its high quality winemaking and aging: fragrant white wines such as Pinot Grigio and Prosecco DOC, and full-bodied red wines such as Raboso, Merlot et Piave DOC. \\r\\nVisit to the estate and the ageing cellars with final tasting of 3 wines.\\r\\nLunch in a typical tavern.\\r\\nIn the afternoon guided tour of Treviso, with the colours of its medieval heart, remodelled and enlarged over the centuries without being misrepresented, bathed by the fresh resurgence waters of rivers and canals, cheerfully tinged with frescoes and decorations. \\r\\nGoodbye dinner in a farmhouse, before returning to your hotel for the night.\"},{\"image_id\":\"257\",\"title\":\"Day 3\",\"desc\":null,\"content\":\"Return to your destination\"}]'),(49,67,'en','Venice Myths & Legends','','<p>An unusual walk through the neighborhoods of Castello and Cannaregio to discover the \"darker\" side of the</p>\n<p>Venetian tradition. In its long history, the city hides many legends, traditions and mysterious facts that will be told by our expert guide: ghost stories, mysterious murders, quarrels. </p>\n<p>Walking in some magnificent and less known places in the city, you will feel like you are living inside a mystery novel. </p>',NULL,'Venice','[{\"title\":\"What are the available days?\",\"content\":\"Tutti i giorni. Sono escluse le Festivit\\u00e0\"},{\"title\":\"Where does the tour start?\",\"content\":\"Piazza San Marco, Porta della Carta di Palazzo Ducale (che corrisponde all\'uscita di Palazzo Ducale)\"},{\"title\":\"Is it recommended for children?\",\"content\":\"Yes\"},{\"title\":\"At what time?\",\"content\":\"From 9 A.M. to 11 A.M. \\r\\nFrom 5 P.M. to 7 P.M.\"}]',22,NULL,'2020-05-03 04:55:12','2020-05-03 04:55:12','{\"0\":{\"title\":\"Available languages: Italian, English, French, German, Italian\"},\"6\":{\"title\":\"Guide available 2 hours\"}}','[{\"title\":\"Transportation\"},{\"title\":\"Extras\"}]',NULL),(50,111,'en','Prealpine Landscapes on Mount Cesen','','<p>Naturalistic excursion on Mount Cesen, the mountain of Valdobbiadene (TV), accompanied by a Nature Guide.</p>\n<p>Mount Cesen is part of the Prealpi Trevigiane, the route winds for the most part on paths from 1000 meters above sea level of Pianezze, the starting point, at an altitude of about 1500 meters above sea level where there are the mountain huts. The itinerary partly follows the European path E7 and the panoramic path TV1, the Alta Via delle Prealpi Trevigiane The localities touched will be: Borri, Lavel, Orsere, Barbaria Mariech, Pianezze.</p>\n<p>Your gaze can wander as far as the lagoon of Venice, the hills below Conegliano Valdobbiadene UNESCO World Heritage Site, the river Piave and the entire Veneto plain. To the north you can admire the chain of the Belluno Dolomites and the ValBelluna below that divides us from them.</p>\n<p>You will walk through woods, pastures and meadows meeting ancient stone farmhouses and wonderful century-old beech trees (some of which are indicated in the list of monumental trees of Veneto) that will tell the history of this territory.</p>\n<p>During spring and early summer wonderful blooms and in autumn a kaleidoscope of colours.</p>\n<p>During the summer, between the beginning of June and the end of September, we suggest a stop in an Alpine hut about 2/3 of the way, to get to know the art of cheese production and taste a lunch of typical products, caressed by the fresh and clean mountain air.</p>',NULL,'Pianezze di Valdobbiadene (TV)','{\"0\":{\"title\":\"What are the available days?\",\"content\":\"May to October every day.\"},\"1\":{\"title\":\"Where does the tour start?\",\"content\":\"Pianezze of Valdobbiadene, near Piazzale del Tempio del Donatore\"},\"3\":{\"title\":\"What time?\",\"content\":\"From 9:30 AM to 3:30 PM\"},\"4\":{\"title\":\"Is it recommended for children?\",\"content\":\"No, minors can only participate if accompanied by an adult.\"},\"5\":{\"title\":\"Difficulty?\",\"content\":\"Medium, suitable for all people who are fairly well-trained in walking, about 9 km long\"},\"6\":{\"title\":\"Difference in height?\",\"content\":\"About 550 mt\"},\"7\":{\"title\":\"Clothing?\",\"content\":\"Comfortable, wear hiking boots, technical clothing, water, energy snacks.\\r\\nuseful trekking poles\\r\\nAny life-saving medication or similar should be brought along during the excursion.\"}}',22,21,'2020-05-07 02:00:26','2020-05-07 02:00:26','{\"0\":{\"title\":\"Languages available: Italian, English, Portuguese\"},\"6\":{\"title\":\"Nature guide\"},\"7\":{\"title\":\"Lunch based on local foods\"},\"8\":{\"title\":\"Visit to the production of alpine cheese\"}}','[{\"title\":\"Transportation\"},{\"title\":\"Extras\"},{\"title\":\"Technical clothing\"}]',NULL),(51,112,'en','Prealpine Landscapes on Mount Cesen','','<p>Naturalistic excursion on Mount Cesen, the mountain of Valdobbiadene (TV), accompanied by a Nature Guide.</p>\n<p>Mount Cesen is part of the Prealpi Trevigiane, the route winds for the most part on paths from 1000 meters above sea level of Pianezze, the starting point, at an altitude of about 1500 meters above sea level where there are the mountain huts. The itinerary partly follows the European path E7 and the panoramic path TV1, the Alta Via delle Prealpi Trevigiane The localities touched will be: Borri, Lavel, Orsere, Barbaria Mariech, Pianezze.</p>\n<p>Your gaze can wander as far as the lagoon of Venice, the hills below Conegliano Valdobbiadene UNESCO World Heritage Site, the river Piave and the entire Veneto plain. To the north you can admire the chain of the Belluno Dolomites and the ValBelluna b